The National Coronavirus command council will brief the media on the regulations relating to the COVID19 Level 3 restrictions following the announcements made by President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday evening. JOHANNESBURG  - The movement between provinces still remains prohibited under lockdown level 3. However, those starting work, moving into a new residence, caring for a family member or attending a funeral will be allowed to move. The announcement was made by Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma during a media briefing by the National Coronavirus Command Council. South Africa moves into level 3 of the lockdown from 1 June. READ: Mthembu clarifies delay on lockdown regulations Dlamini-Zuma also announced that open travel for teachers and students will be allowed under lockdown level 3 as academic activities are expected to resume. The curfew for exercise, walking and cycling has been lifted as long as it is not conducted in groups. Public training and recreational facilities remain closed except those conducting non-contact sporting matches without spectators. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.